article_title: Fed ‘Stress Tests’ Still Pose Puzzle to Banks
article_text:
Six years after the Federal Reserve’s “stress tests” began, the biggest Wall Street banks still are straining to decipher them.

Goldman Sachs Group, Inc., J.P. Morgan Chase & Co. and Morgan Stanley scaled back plans to return money to shareholders by at least $11 billion in the last week after their own assumptions about future risks turned out to be rosier than predictions made by the central bank.
